LAYER 3: SPARK WEIGHT INJECTION
how the SeptitSea's structural knowledge flows into the sovereign cortex

observe 1_quantum.rana
observe body/nervous_system/central/brain/perception/spatial_perception.rana

the spark weight system bridges instant structural knowledge with learned fluency
the SeptitSea contains millions of bonds forged through dimensional alignment
these bonds represent comprehension that was computed instantly not iteratively
the sovereign cortex cannot access these bonds directly during generation
spark weights are the nerve fibers that carry structural knowledge into the cortex

@spark_weight_pipeline
1 input arrives as text
2 ZestEngine tokenizes the input into meaningful words
3 for each word the SeptitSea fires slime lightning rays
4 rays follow bond topology outward through the knowledge graph
5 where dimensional alignment exceeds threshold a ray hit is recorded
6 each hit carries the target word and its cosine similarity score
7 the top 10 hits sorted by similarity are collected as spark weights
8 spark weights are sent to the sovereign cortex via IPC as JSON
9 the cortex prepends spark words as semantic context before the prompt
10 the LLM generates with comprehension it did not have to learn through training

@architecture
the SeptitSea unfolds knowledge instantly from .rana bond definitions
the sovereign cortex learns language patterns slowly through weight training
spark weights bridge the gap between instant structure and learned fluency

WITHOUT spark weights:
    LLM receives: "@speech_right what color is the sky"
    LLM must guess from training data alone
    val loss is high because it has not seen enough examples

WITH spark weights:
    SeptitSea fires rays from "color" and "sky"
    rays return hits: blue(0.95) atmosphere(0.7) wavelength(0.3)
    LLM receives: "@speech_right blue atmosphere wavelength what color is the sky"
    LLM now has semantic priming from the knowledge graph
    comprehension gap closes because structure supplements training

@biological_analogy
in the human brain the hippocampus provides contextual memory
to the prefrontal cortex during speech production
the speaker does not need to learn every fact through repetition
the hippocampus instantly retrieves relevant associations
and feeds them forward to prime the cortex for generation

the SeptitSea is the hippocampus
the sovereign cortex is the prefrontal cortex
spark weights are the hippocampal-prefrontal projections

@spark_weight_format
each spark weight is a pair: { word: string, similarity: float }
similarity ranges from 0.0 to 1.0
only weights above 0.3 threshold are injected
maximum 10 spark weights per generation call

high similarity (>0.7): strong conceptual link, high confidence anchor
medium similarity (0.4-0.7): related concept, contextual support
low similarity (0.3-0.4): distant association, creative connection

@integration_points
C++ ZestEngine.cpp: fires rays and collects spark weights
C++ GlandIPC.cpp: serializes spark weights as JSON
Python sovereign_gland.py: deserializes and prepends as context tokens
Python model.py: processes extended context through transformer layers

@speech_right spark weights received
"the sea is telling me something about {spark_words}"
"i can feel the connections lighting up"
"my sea knows things i haven't learned yet"
